{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Combobox · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Combobox</h1>
    <p class="lead">A searchable trigger for picking from a list of values.</p>
    <p>Reach for Combobox when the option set is too long to scan visually, or when users should be able to add their own values. Multi-select shows chips inside the trigger. Tagging mode lets users create unknown values on the fly. For a non-searchable picker that looks the same, use <a class="link" href="/select">Select</a>.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-stisla-combobox</code> to a <code>&lt;select class="combobox"&gt;</code>. The original element stays in the DOM (hidden) so form submission works as authored. Type to filter.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="basicCombo" class="field__label">Country</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="basicCombo" name="country" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Search countries">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="id">Indonesia</option>
        <option value="my">Malaysia</option>
        <option value="sg">Singapore</option>
        <option value="ph">Philippines</option>
        <option value="th">Thailand</option>
        <option value="vn">Vietnam</option>
        <option value="bn">Brunei</option>
        <option value="kh">Cambodia</option>
        <option value="la">Laos</option>
        <option value="mm">Myanmar</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Installation</h2>
    <p>Skip this step if you're on the <code>stisla-full</code> bundle, it already ships with Combobox. On the core <code>stisla</code> bundle, add it alongside as a script tag or via your package manager.</p>

    <div class="tabs mt-4" data-stisla-tabs>
      <div class="tabs__list">
        <button class="tabs__trigger" data-value="compiled">Compiled</button>
        <button class="tabs__trigger" data-value="manual">Manual</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs__panel" data-value="compiled">
        <p>Add the component's stylesheet and script next to the ones loading the core bundle.</p>
        {% call ui.code(lang='html') %}
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@stisla/css@beta/dist/components/combobox.css">
        <script type="module" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@stisla/vanilla@beta/dist/components/combobox.js"></script>
        {% endcall %}
        <p>The script auto-registers on the global <code>Stisla</code> instance, so no extra wiring is needed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs__panel" data-value="manual">
        <p>Import the CSS and the JS. Both files register themselves on load, so no manual <code>register()</code> or <code>Stisla.init()</code> call is needed.</p>
        {% call ui.code(lang='js') %}
        import '@stisla/css/components/combobox';
        import '@stisla/vanilla/components/combobox';
        {% endcall %}
        <p>Tom Select rides along as a transitive dependency of <code>@stisla/vanilla</code>, so no extra install is needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Keyboard</h2>
    <p>The trigger behaves like a searchable picker. Focus lands in the search input as soon as the popup opens.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><kbd>ArrowDown</kbd> / <kbd>ArrowUp</kbd>: move highlight through the filtered list</li>
      <li><kbd>Enter</kbd>: pick the highlighted option (creates a new tag in tagging mode)</li>
      <li><kbd>Escape</kbd>: close the popup</li>
      <li><kbd>Backspace</kbd>: remove the last chip in multi mode when the search input is empty</li>
      <li>Type any letter: filter the list</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multiple</h2>
    <p>Add <code>multiple</code> to let users pick several values. Each chosen value shows as a chip with an inline remove handle.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="multiCombo" class="field__label">Tags</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="multiCombo" name="tags" multiple data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Add tags">
        <option value="bug">Bug</option>
        <option value="docs" selected>Docs</option>
        <option value="feat" selected>Feature</option>
        <option value="qa">QA</option>
        <option value="perf">Performance</option>
        <option value="a11y">Accessibility</option>
        <option value="i18n">Internationalization</option>
        <option value="security">Security</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tagging</h2>
    <p>Set <code>data-stisla-combobox-create="true"</code> to let users add values that aren't in the list. The new value lands in the options as the user presses Enter.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="tagsCombo" class="field__label">Topics</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="tagsCombo" name="topics" multiple data-stisla-combobox data-stisla-combobox-create="true" data-placeholder="Type and press Enter">
        <option value="design" selected>Design</option>
        <option value="frontend">Frontend</option>
        <option value="backend">Backend</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.combobox--compact</code> or <code>.combobox--roomy</code> for the small or large variant. Sizes match the input scale.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <select class="combobox combobox--compact" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Small" aria-label="Small combobox">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
      <select class="combobox" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Default" aria-label="Default combobox">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
      <select class="combobox combobox--roomy" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Large" aria-label="Large combobox">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Option groups</h2>
    <p>Wrap related options in <code>&lt;optgroup&gt;</code> to label sections inside the popup. Search runs against the option labels; the group label is just a header.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="groupedCombo" class="field__label">City</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="groupedCombo" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Search cities">
        <option value=""></option>
        <optgroup label="Indonesia">
          <option value="jkt">Jakarta</option>
          <option value="bdg">Bandung</option>
          <option value="sby">Surabaya</option>
        </optgroup>
        <optgroup label="Malaysia">
          <option value="kul">Kuala Lumpur</option>
          <option value="pen">Penang</option>
        </optgroup>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Disabled</h2>
    <p>Add <code>disabled</code> to block interaction. The wrapper picks up <code>.disabled</code> from Tom Select automatically.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="disabledCombo" class="field__label">Plan</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="disabledCombo" data-stisla-combobox disabled>
        <option value="free" selected>Free</option>
        <option value="pro">Pro</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Browser validation</h2>
    <p>Native HTML constraints gate form submission as they would on a native <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>. Add <code>required</code> with an empty placeholder <code>&lt;option value=""&gt;</code> and the form blocks until the user picks a real value. The browser's tooltip is suppressed because it would anchor to the hidden source, so render the error text with <code>.field__error</code>. The wrapper picks up the danger border automatically when constraints fail and clears it once the new value is valid.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <form class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;" onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); alert('submitted');">
      <div class="field">
        <label for="reqCombo" class="field__label">Plan</label>
        <select class="combobox" id="reqCombo" name="plan" required data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Pick a plan">
          <option value=""></option>
          <option value="free">Free</option>
          <option value="pro">Pro</option>
          <option value="team">Team</option>
        </select>
        <div class="field__description">Hit Submit without picking. The wrapper paints invalid and the search input takes focus. Pick any option and the red clears on its own.</div>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">Submit</button>
    </form>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Invalid</h2>
    <p>Set <code>aria-invalid="true"</code> on the source <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>. The wrapper picks it up via <code>:has()</code> and paints the danger border.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="invalidCombo" class="field__label">Plan</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="invalidCombo" data-stisla-combobox aria-invalid="true" aria-describedby="invalidComboError" data-placeholder="Pick a plan">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="free">Free</option>
        <option value="pro">Pro</option>
        <option value="team">Team</option>
      </select>
      <div id="invalidComboError" class="field__error">This plan isn't available in your region.</div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Events</h2>
    <p>Listen for <code>stisla:combobox:change</code> to react to selection changes. The event's <code>detail.value</code> is a string for single, an array for multi.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="eventCombo" class="field__label">Tag</label>
      <select class="combobox" id="eventCombo" data-stisla-combobox data-placeholder="Pick a tag">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="bug">Bug</option>
        <option value="docs">Docs</option>
        <option value="feat">Feature</option>
      </select>
      <div id="eventComboOut" class="field__description">Current: (none)</div>
    </div>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var el = document.getElementById('eventCombo');
        var out = document.getElementById('eventComboOut');
        el.addEventListener('stisla:combobox:change', function (e) {
          out.textContent = 'Current: ' + (e.detail.value || '(none)');
        });
      })();
    </script>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>The trigger ships its own <code>--combobox-*</code> variables that mirror the input surface. The popup adds more <code>--combobox-*</code> variables that follow the same surface recipe as <a class="link" href="/menu">Menu</a> and <a class="link" href="/select">Select</a>.</p>
    <p>On touch devices (<code>@media (pointer: coarse)</code>) <code>--combobox-font-size</code> is bumped to <code>1rem</code> so iOS Safari doesn't zoom the viewport on focus. The browser auto-zooms any field with computed font-size below 16px and never zooms back; desktop keeps the tighter default.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-height</code></td><td>Trigger height; multi treats this as a floor and grows with chip rows</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-padding-inline</code></td><td>Trigger horizontal padding</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-radius</code></td><td>Corner radius, shared by trigger and popup; chips inset from it</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-indicator</code></td><td>Chevron SVG; data: URL with literal stroke per theme</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-bg</code></td><td>Surface, shared by trigger and popup</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-item-bg-hover</code></td><td>Highlighted row background</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--combobox-item-bg-active</code></td><td>Currently-selected row background</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
